RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 6 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOT MOJO was urged at the break, obtained a clear lead then was put to rating tactics dictating the pace racing just off the rail, faced pressure up the backstretch, drifted out leaving the far turn, was headed at the top of the stretch, dug in under left-handed urging and regained command by mid-stretch to inch away late. JACKS SPRING BREAK broke a half-step slowly then was encouraged forward but caught outside four to five wide on the first turn, pursued from outside into the far turn mounting a bid turning for home, obtained a narrow lead briefly in upper stretch but was outfinished while clear of the rest. KWIK stalked from between runners then edged closer to press two to three wide up the backstretch, was encouraged along three furlongs out while losing ground, altered inside the leaders about the five-sixteenths, ran on evenly in the stretch. WAVERUNNER settled off the pace racing just off the inside, came out wider turning for home, failed to menace. TOAH pressed the pace from between runners three to four wide up the backstretch and far turn, weakened thereafter. LIMBO'S PROMISE tracked from inside saving ground, failed to rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked inside, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Got Mojo
ENTRY.COMMENT: urge brk, pace, off rail, drift bit past 1/4, headed 3/16, dug in

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, off rail, came out, no menace

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 2-3w btw, ask 3/8, alter in 5/16, evenly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Toah
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 3-4w btw, weakened

ENTRY.COMMENT: 1/2 step slow brk, 4-5w, bid & brief lead 3/16, outfinished

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HONEY CREEK settled just off the pace, advanced outside a rival pursuing the leader heading up the backstretch, drew even about the five-sixteenths racing about three wide, took a narrow lead by the top of the stretch, dueled till nearing the sixteenth pole then edged clear under steady urging. CAT TALE BREEZE moved clear to dictate terms racing off the fence, was engaged midway on the turn, dueled gamely till late stretch then yielded grudgingly. GOTOTHEWINDOW chased the early pace, steadily weakened. GOSPEL FLOW raced off the pace, was placed in tight quarters by the riderless horse near the three-eighths, failed to rally. PREACH IT GIRL veered in at the break, lost the rider, walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KODALINE broke a bit awkwardly spotting the field a bit over a length then settled at the rear while shifting in, made a rapid advance inside midway up the backstretch to contend for the lead at the half, dueled through the turn and was put to a drive about the quarter, drifted about a bit in the stretch and edged clear under stout urging. TREASURE COAST raced just off the leading pair three wide through the first turn, took closer order leaving the first turn and was carried out by a drifting rival, moved back in and regained position to vie for the lead outside three deep through the far turn, proved no match for the winner but held the place over GRANDSONSAM, who tucked in at the rear racing outside the eventual winner, advanced in tandem with that one nearing the half to vie for the lead from between runners, lacked the needed late kick and was outfinished for second. STAPLETON SONG moved forward inside to contest the early lead around the first turn, was steadily getting out heading up the backstretch, moved back nearer inside into the first turn, failed to rally. BARN SHARK was urged forward at the break, dueled around the first turn, was carried out heading up the backstretch, angled in and moved back forward from between runners to vie for the lead three wide late up the backstretch, began to weaken entering the far turn and was empty thereafter.
